# **Mainframe Usage, Reporting & BA Role in Group Disability Projects**

## 1. Role of Mainframe Systems in Group Disability

In Group Disability (STD & LTD), the **mainframe remains the system of record** for core policy, plan, and claim data. Modern front‑end applications do **not replace** the mainframe; instead, they **orchestrate and retrieve data from it**.

### Key Mainframe Responsibilities

*   Storage of **policy master data** (PAS/EAS DB2 tables)
*   Storage of **claim‑level data**
*   Execution of **business rules** via application and data layer programs
*   Generating **regulatory and operational reports**

The interaction pattern is consistently:

> Front‑end app → CICS Webservice → Application Layer Program → Data Layer → DB2 Tables

This architecture is explicitly documented in the **Disability Claims Tracking (DCT)** workflow. [\[DCT (Disab...Tracking) \| Confluence\]](https://prd-can-lifeco.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/GCKH/pages/176943345/DCT+Disability+Claims+Tracking)

