## 3. Reports Generated from the Mainframe (Group Disability)

### 3.1 Operational & Financial Reports

One confirmed example is the **YMFR (Yearly Monthly Financial Report)**:

*   Report ID pattern: `CS14.YMFR.REPORT.G*`
*   Used for **Group Disability financial reconciliation**
*   Generated directly from mainframe jobs
*   Requested and tracked via intake tickets

This is a **production‑run mainframe report**, not an analytic dashboard. [\[GITB-11767...Disability \| Jira\]](https://prd-can-lifeco.atlassian.net/browse/GITB-11767)

### 3.2 Plan Provision & Claim Reports

From DCT, users generate:

*   **PPS (Plan Provision Summary)** reports
*   Printed STD and LTD plan outputs
*   Claim‑specific extracts routed via data layers (G‑series programs)

These reports rely on:

*   DB2 table joins
*   Data layer program routing
*   Defined copybooks

 [\[DCT (Disab...Tracking) \| Confluence\]](https://prd-can-lifeco.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/GCKH/pages/176943345/DCT+Disability+Claims+Tracking)

