## 4. Business Analyst Role in Group Disability Mainframe Projects

In Group Disability, BAs act as **translation and control points** between:

*   Business users (claims, operations)
*   Mainframe developers
*   Digital / data platforms

### Core BA Responsibilities

#### 4.1 Requirements & Business Rules

*   Document **plan provisions**, eligibility rules, and claim logic
*   Translate business language into **mainframe‑consumable rules**
*   Validate whether logic belongs in:
    *   Application layer
    *   Data layer
    *   Front‑end only

Supported by DCT and Ultera documentation. [\[DCT (Disab...Tracking) \| Confluence\]](https://prd-can-lifeco.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/GCKH/pages/176943345/DCT+Disability+Claims+Tracking), [\[Disability...tion (RAG) \| Confluence\]](https://prd-can-lifeco.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/GCKH/pages/836469099/Disability+Retrieval+Augmented+Generation+RAG)

#### 4.2 Data Mapping & Lineage

*   Map UI fields (e.g., PPS screen fields) to:
    *   Mainframe copybooks
    *   DB2 tables
*   Identify required keys (Claim ID, Office ID, COPI)
*   Document **source‑to‑target mappings**

These mappings are essential for mainframe SQL validation. [\[DCT (Disab...Tracking) \| Confluence\]](https://prd-can-lifeco.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/GCKH/pages/176943345/DCT+Disability+Claims+Tracking)

#### 4.3 Report Enablement

*   Define report scope (e.g., YMFR, PPS)
*   Identify:
    *   Required parameters
    *   Output format
    *   Frequency
*   Coordinate job execution and UAT validation

 [\[GITB-11767...Disability \| Jira\]](https://prd-can-lifeco.atlassian.net/browse/GITB-11767)

#### 4.4 Access & Controls (Supporting Role)

*   Participate in access discussions when mainframe data flows to analytics or reporting platforms
*   Validate role‑based access assumptions for downstream consumers

